  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Retail internships in Oxfam shops</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will target BME women specifically and will provide supported retail internships within Oxfam shops in West Yorkshire and East Lancashire.  It is anticipated that women will carry out an internship of six months.  Interns will receive specific retail training as well as out of pocket expenses including childcare.  Interns will be supported to work flexible hours around caring responsibilities. It is expected that interns will be in a strong position to apply for shop manager positions within Oxfam, as well as other retail management positions elsewhere. The main costs for the project are for expenses and training.</narrative>
  </description>
